                        <p>Just a few weeks after his book was released, Holmes and Balwani were each charged with two counts of conspiracy to commit wire fraud and nine counts of wire fraud.</p>
<p>Carreyrou said the the criminal proceedings will mark the final chapter in the Theranos saga and set a precedent for the treatment of startup founders who ignore ethics to make it big in Silicon Valley.</p>
<p>“If she gets off after everything that’s happened—the hundreds of millions of dollars that were defrauded from investors, but also the way patients were put in harm’s way—it could be a signal to Silicon Valley that it’s business as usual,” he said. “On the other hand, if she does get convicted and she does prison time, it would be a wake-up call.”</p>

